race.comment: The Group 1 Oakleigh Plate and we're siding with the resuming TROPICUS (3). He won the G3 The Heath over this route first up last preparation in slick time, leading throughout to score by 2.25 lengths. 58.5kg is no easy feat but this isn't a particularly strong edition and he's the right sort of horse to sit on speed and absorb pressure. POINT BARROW (14) resumes as the sole 3yo in the race. She's very progressive having reeled off some big wins from well back last time in. 50kg here is attractive but she'll likely be giving some very fast horses a decent headstart. GEEGEES MISTRUTH (10) ran a good race fresh here when charging home over 1000m. Up in trip and down in weight suits. OAK HILL (5) won the G2 Rubiton here last time and will be charging late at each way odds. GALLANT SON (13) has won both this time in and gets in well with improvement to come.
